class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {
        int n = nums.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; ++j) {
                if (nums[i] + nums[j] == target) {
                    return new int[]{i, j};
                }
            }
        }
        return new int[0];
    }
}


**Explanation**

This is a very standard two pointer problem.
The two pointer approach is the following:

Start the two pointers at the beginning and end of the array.
If the two pointer sum is less than the target, increment the pointer to the right.
If the two pointer sum is greater than the target, decrement the pointer to the left.
If the two pointer sum equals the target, return the indices of the two pointers.

